                        <interp inst="t18450616-name-574" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY LANGDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman in the service of Edward Marma<lb></lb>duke Clark, an optician, in the Strand—the prisoner was in his employ—I on the evening of the 22nd of May, or the morning of the 23rd, I gave him a telescope which we had had to repair, to take to Mr. Gahagan's, in the Strand—this now produced is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What were the prisoner's wages? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a week—he did not sleep in the house—he kept himself.</p>
